rawText: Your morning coffee is best when served with views of snowy hoodoos. #VisitUtah

Utah snow forecaster Evan Thayer (pictured here enjoying this week's fresh powder) gave us a #WeatherWednesday update at @brightonresort on upcoming ski conditions. Head over to our Instagram Story to watch. #VisitUtah
#NationalMuttDay is the perfect time to treat your furry best friend with a memorable adventure. Link in bio to search dog-friendly areas throughout Utah. #VisitUtah
Discover the heart of St. George’s awe-inspiring art scene starting at #Kayenta and its impressive Coyote Gulch Art Village. #VisitUtah

Spanning high-elevation peaks, wild plateaus, deep canyons and towering sandstone, Bears Ears National Monument is imbued with layers of culture — layers of life. The only way to understand the depths of this landscape is to listen to the locals who connect with the land in their own distinct ways. Watch our Instagram Story for a sneak preview of our "Voices of Bears Ears" four-part series. #VisitUtah
Have you hit the slopes yet? 6 #Utah ski resorts are now open! Watch our Instagram Story for this morning's #WeatherWednesday snow report at @snowbasinresort. #VisitUtah

Our weekly snow report #WeatherWednesdays is back starting tomorrow with Evan Thayer of @findopensnow! Tune into our Instagram Live tomorrow at 9:30 am MT as we look ahead to this weekend's ski conditions. #VisitUtah
Marvel at 2,000 years of Native American stories etched on Newspaper Rock in #IndianCreek. Remember: always visit these historical sites with care and respect. #VisitUtah

This Thanksgiving, we're thankful for the gift of travel and the opportunity to experience spectacular places, people, culture and history with the ones we love most. #HappyThanksgiving, fellow adventurers! #VisitUtah
Getting ready for a snowy holiday weekend of skiing or boarding? So is @pcski's new avalanche dog Maple! Photo by: @PCski #VisitUtah
Happy 99th birthday, @zionnps! Commemorate this day by posting your favorite #ZionNationalPark photo using #YesVisitUtah for a chance to be featured.
That blissful moment when you reach the end of a trail and take in the stillness all around you. Which trail are you exploring today for #NationalHikingDay? #VisitUtah
Experience Dixie National Forest like you’ve never seen it before in @yourforestsyourfuture's new film. Watch it now on our IGTV. #VisitUtah
On this day 47 years ago, the U.S. designated Arches National Park and its staggering 2,000+ natural arches. PC: @nationalparkservice #VisitUtah

In honor of #VeteransDay tomorrow, the @nationalparkservice is offering #FreeEntranceDay at any national park, monument, recreation area and historic site. Visit the link in our bio to find one near you. #VisitUtah
The leaves may be dropping, but photos of our gorgeous fall foliage are here to stay. PC: @reago.my.eggo #VisitUtah
Anyone else daydreaming of #ski season? It's about that time to start planning a powder trip of a lifetime. #VisitUtah

Just another day on the range for this 2,000-pound bison. Last week, the annual #AntelopeIsland Bison Roundup took place with trained men and women wrangling a herd of 500 free-roaming bison. #NationalBisonDay #VisitUtah

@shesmercedes traveled to the breathtaking backcountry of #Moab to feature Utah climber @highsteph. Preview her extraordinary journey now on our Instagram Story. #DefineYourPath #VisitUtah PC: @janvincentkleine
Fit for all adventure seekers, a hike in Little Cottonwood Canyon offers spectacular fall snapshots. #VisitUtah
#SanRafaelSwell showcases nature's geologic artwork formed over thousands of years into a unique assembly of sandstone buttresses, canyons and plateaus. #VisitUtah PC: Dean Krakel

@utahroyalsfc pro soccer player @erika_tymrak reveling in the stellar views of Peek-a-Boo Slot Canyon – one of many stops on her very own #Utah getaway this week! Take a look back at her adventures in our Story Highlights. #VisitUtah

The votes are in and now it’s time for us to send @utahroyalsfc pro soccer player @erika_tymrak on her own Utah getaway. Follow along on our Instagram Story as she travels this week to hidden gems like the Coral Pink Sand Dunes State Park, Best Friends Animal Sanctuary, Peek-a-Boo and Spooky Slot Canyons and much more. #VisitUtah
#LaSalMountains loom beyond purple hues and ancient lithified dunes of 200-million-year-old sandstone. #VisitUtah
A moderate hike to Buffalo Point at #AntelopeIsland offers rewarding views stretching 75 miles across the #GreatSaltLake. #VisitUtah
Fall adds another pop of color to already exceptional views. #VisitUtah

Take in the splendor of the night sky above Kodachrome Basin State Park's 67 monolithic stone spires. At 5,800 feet above sea level, in October days are beautiful and overnight temps are chilly. #VisitUtah PC: @irockutah
From Bear Lake to Wasatch Mountain, get ready for this year’s tapestry of red, orange and yellow. #VisitUtah
Wade upstream, as walls rise to a thousand feet high. The Narrows is one slot canyon adventure you won't want to miss. PC: David Pettit #ZionNationalPark #VisitUtah PC: David Pettit
Fall colors surround #StewartFalls as a reward to hikers as they move through aspen trees, over creeks, and through alpine meadows. #VisitUtah
It is difficult to rival Monument Valley's sense of expansiveness. #VisitUtah PC: @dylankato
Moab, Utah offers climbers all the challenges they can handle. PC: @mtbbonnie #VisitUtah
The Spiral Jetty's black basalt rocks form a 1,500-foot-long coil in the Great Salt Lake — now that's a work of art! PC: @glitchlov3 #VisitUtah
Carved by Utah's Green and Colorado rivers, this national park is no stranger to 527-square miles of dramatic desert landscape. Happy 54th birthday, Canyonlands National Park. PC: Tom Till #VisitUtah
Come for the rock art, dinosaurs, and mountain biking, stay for the wide-open spaces. PC: Marc Piscotty #VisitUtah #EmeryCounty
A 30,000-acre expanse of barren beauty. PC: @davidmrule #VisitUtah
This sure-footed climber is well worth seeking out. #VisitUtah #mountaingoat
Get to know Hovenweep National Monument — even after hours, this monument knows how to draw a crowd in the desert valley. #VisitUtah

As summer lingers into fall, celebrate the more northern latitude's lush forest landscapes. Head north of the 41st parallel to the top of Utah for that hard-to-find getaway you've been searching for. #VisitUtah
Located in the south end of Provo Canyon, Bridal Veil Falls is one of several impressive waterfalls to see in Utah Valley. PC: @garth_rogers #VisitUtah
Seeking some of the most brilliant landscapes in Utah? Gunsight Butte offers just that. #VisitUtah

The road to the River House Ruin requires four-wheel drive and high clearance, but is certainly worth it. From pioneer history to Ancestral Puebloan ruins, this house with a view is an adventure for the whole family. PC: Jo Savage #VisitUtah
See Utah from a new perspective. This weekend presents the annual Ogden Valley Balloon & Artist Festival. PC: Matt Morgan #VisitUtah
Between walls of sandstone fins, find your #darksky moment in Devil's Garden. PC: @irockutah
Renowned for its red sand beaches, this 1,322-acre reservoir has a variety of activities for all ages. #VisitUtah
The meditative eleven-circuit Desert Rose Labyrinth and sculpture garden welcomes all visitors to southern Utah. PC: Anna Papuga #VisitUtah #Kayenta
Spark your imagination, Capitol Reef National Park is surrounded by striking copper-colored rock and expansive vistas. PC: Aleksandr Mironyuk #VisitUtah
Transforming the landscape of the vast desert, Skull Valley's Horseshoe Springs offers a little-known water world. PC: Eric Erlenbusch. #VisitUtah

Less than 15 feet of rushing water, this family-friendly hike to a waterfall in Payson Canyon, part of the Nebo Loop National Scenic Byway, is an adventure you won't want to miss. PC: Emily Sierra #VisitUtah
Take in the view of Canyonlands National Park from a different perspective. Ride the rapids and flat water of the Green River and see how it helped form this remarkable landscape. #VisitUtah
Exploring the winding canyons around southern Utah is an experience you won’t soon forget. PC: Aleksandr Mironyuk #VisitUtah
Wildflower season paints summer meadows. PC: @jszphotos #VisitUtah
Looking for a rewarding hike? Pack your water shoes and head to Kanarraville Falls. #VisitUtah PC: Eric Erlenbusch
Drawing boaters and anglers year-round, this spectacular red rock desert boasts some of the warmest waters in the state. #VisitUtah
Ogden Valley is a serene, pastoral landscape steeped in frontier history. PC: @jaydashphotography #VisitUtah
Red rock hoodoos by day, Milky Way Mecca by night. PC: @suedeonfilm #VisitUtah #darkskies
Seven miles east of Ogden, Pineview Reservoir is a year-round recreation utopia. PC: Jay Dash #VisitUtah
Challenge yourself with this geological whimsy and discover your own goblins. #VisitUtah PC: @hansiphoto
Sneak a peek out of a red rock window! At Bryce Canyon National Park, some hoodoos reach up to 150 feet high. #VisitUtah PC: @_steelemeaway_
Launch your kayak into the deep blue of Tony Grove Lake. #VisitUtah
Eleven recognized islands and one unforgettable sunset. PC: Matt Morgan #VisitUtah
Over 30,000 acres of West Desert. #VisitUtah
Summer has officially arrived to set the backdrop for this freestanding, sandstone pinnacle located along the Green River. PC: Tom Till #VisitUtah #firstdayofsummer
Not every hike has a payoff — but we think the best ones do. #VisitUtah
Adventure like a local and you'll discover this desert #oasis. #VisitUtah #desert
Looking for a place to park the RV this summer? Utah’s 329 public campgrounds have the answer. #visitutah #camping #campinglife #adventure
The sprawling 60,000-acre Red Cliffs Desert Reserve is a one-of-a-kind geographic treasure that protects delicate landscapes and the threatened desert tortoise. #VisitUtah
Just north of Salt Lake City, Davis County's sunsets and wildflowers seem endless. #VisitUtah #wildflowers
Sculpted by wind and time, Snow Canyon’s sandstone cliffs share the same geology as nearby Zion National Park. #VisitUtah Photo: Audrey Livingston
Find tranquil moments beneath soaring fins, pinnacles and spires. Photo: @giselewyne #VisitUtah #utahyoga #adventure #fishertowers #roadtrip
The Valley of the Gods is perhaps one of the most intriguing destinations in San Juan County. With idyllic sandstone structures, it doesn't get more Utah than this. #VisitUtah #hiking #adventure

The Provo River is a top tailwater fishery. The Middle and Lower sections of the river offer 15+ miles of angling access, prolific hatches and stunning views. Photo: Adam Barker #VisitUtah #fishing #flyfishing

Mixed with unique history and geology, Canyonlands National Park is a landscape dominated by rock. Erosion has sculpted, sliced, and shaped the bedrock into cliffs, pinnacles, flying buttresses, minarets and rounded domes. Enjoy the natural beauty for yourself this spring. #visitutah #findyourpark #adventure
As the spring weather streams through Moab, we are reminded of the natural beauty this beloved national park has to offer. #VisitUtah #findyourpark #hikingadventures
The promise of an underground maze lures you upward — 6,730 feet above sea level, to be exact. 📸: Jay Drowns #VisitUtah #nowopen
No difficult climbs or drop-offs at this 150 million-year-old, sandstone wonder. PC: Tom Till #VisitUtah #findyourpark #zionnationalpark
Looking for a quaint getaway? Butterfly Lake has more to offer than just its natural butterfly shape. #VisitUtah

On May 10, 1869, the presidents of the Union Pacific and Central Pacific railroad met in Promontory, Utah and drove a ceremonial last spike into a rail line that connected their railroads. This made transcontinental railroad travel possible for the first time in the U.S. #VisitUtah #history #nps
Celebrate National Travel and Tourism Week with whimsical views that look a little something like this. 📸: Michael Kunde #travelnow #nttw18 #VisitUtah
Experience a home away from home this summer. Light up your evening, nestled in the Looking Glass Arch. #VisitUtah #camping #adventure
At dusk, a trek through the Uinta Mountains is worth the stunning stream views and shimmering lakes teaming with fish. #flyfishing #fishing #VisitUtah PC: Frank Jensen
Spend enough time in the Moab-area and you may just discover this hidden desert waterfall. #VisitUtah #WaterfallWednesday #Wanderlust PC: Tom Till
Perched along the north slope of the Uinta Mountains, this 11,500 foot Red Castle Peak holds a prominent place on the Utah skyline. #VisitUtah PC: Frank Jensen
Cast a fly into Green River's emerald waters near Flaming Gorge and you'll soon understand why so many anglers consider this a must-fish river. #VisitUtah #fishing #flyfishing
This spring, broaden your horizons and experience that bucket-list #Utah park you have been waiting to see! #VisitUtah #findyourpark #wanderlust PC: Jay Drowns
There are few places better than #Utah to view the cosmos. Join us and turn your eyes toward the stars during International Dark Sky Week. #VisitUtah #IDSW2018 #stargazing #darkskies
Formed by the cutting force of water and a true testament to the power of nature and time, can you guess which spectacular #Utah monument was designated today? #VisitUtah 📸: Mel Lewis
A chance encounter with a wild mustang is always a possibility as you wind along the dirt road backways of Utah's West Desert. 📸: Rosie Serago #VisitUtah

The Mighty 5® national parks are definitely something to rave about. Plan a trip to Southern Utah and experience Canyonlands National Park's waves of distinctive sandstone spires. #VisitUtah 📸: Neal Herbert
Spring is in the air and Mother Nature is in charge of the show! Enjoy all the colors of the rainbow during the annual Thanksgiving Point Tulip Festival. #VisitUtah

Magnificent #sunsets are even closer than you think. The Great Salt Lake is only 30 minutes from downtown #SaltLakeCity and provides magical views as day turns to night. #LifeElevated. PC: Matt Morgan
Discover one of Utah’s most scenic highways and a drive just as beautiful as the destination. #VisitUtah

Adventure where the weekend warriors brand the earth with their footprints and desert hues blend into the golden alpenglow. At Coral Pink Sand Dunes State Park, more than 2,000 acres of rippling sand awaits! #VisitUtah 📸: Matt Gee

Like many of us, Capitol Reef National Park is Prajit Ravidran’s favorite National Park. Prajit was able to complete the entire 60-mile Cathedral Valley loop last year. #VisitUtah #darkskies 📸: @irockutah

Take a look at this incredible #darkskies self portrait of Ambassador, Prajit Ravindran! This panorama was shot at Bryce Canyon National Park. Due to its high elevation of 8,000-9,000 feet, the skies are very clear and perfect for a night photoshoot. #VisitUtah 📸: @irockutah

Utah Ambassador, Prajit Ravindran, shares with us a unique lighting technique at Arches National Park. Prajit created the ring of fire by moving around the tree with a LED lamp in his hand. #VisitUtah #darkskies 📸: @irockutah

Ever since photographer Prajit Ravindran moved to Utah, the Bonneville Salt Flats have been one of his favorite places to shoot. The dark sky photographer says, “The Salt Flats put on a unique show every visit — there is less light pollution facing South, which results in good opportunities for photographing the night skies.” #VisitUtah #darkskies 📸: @irockutah

Rugged and gnarly, White Pocket will impress even the most adventurous explorer with its abundant marble swirls and varied landscape. It’s worth every second of the long drive on deep, sandy roads, but make sure you have a high-clearance vehicle with four-wheel-drive! 📸: John Fowler #VisitUtah

Are you looking to experience a variety of outdoor adventures in Utah? Look no further than Zion National Park! Hikers of all abilities will find trails that lead to sweeping vistas, clear pools, natural arches and narrow canyons. #VisitUtah #LifeElevated 📸: Matt Morgan

With spring's arrival and warmer weather on the way, you can expect to see wildflowers in full bloom. Take an intimate look at Flaming Gorge as the canyon walls catch the fire of the intense morning light! #VisitUtah

Spend three days indulging in Moab’s softer side — experience the intrinsic value of the the 234 mile adventure from Moab to Salt Lake City. Discover hidden trails that thread through iconic rustic rock canyons, raft down the mighty Colorado and more! #VisitUtah #LifeElevated 📸: Barry Gutierrez

This spring, explore pristine deserts, sandstone peaks and flat-topped hills encompassing Factory #Butte. Awaiting the arrival of venture seekers — this 6,302 foot eroded summit stands tall to the east of Capitol Reef National Park. #Explore #VisitUtah #LifeElevated

Leave the bustle of modern civilization behind — the road to Antelope Island State Park is 25 miles north of Salt Lake City. Home to 36 miles of hiking trails and free-roaming bison and antelope herds, this is a must-do adventure destination. 📸: Dan Ransom

Stack your itinerary for a complete adventure destination this spring! Surrounded by a sea of bizarre hoodoos and amazing geology, Bryce Canyon National Park is a whimsical journey from start to finish. #VisitUtah

Lying south of Bluff via Highway 163 on the Utah and Arizona border, is Monument Valley Navajo Tribal Park — the iconic symbol of the American West and sacred heart of the Navajo Nation. The rugged, ancestral infused desert hosts towering sandstone rock formations that have been sculpted over time and soar 400 to 1,000 feet above the valley floor. #VisitUtah

A Milky Way glow sets the stage for Delicate Arch, making a nighttime debut. Overlooking a slickrock basin, the silhouette of the La Sal Mountains shadow the iconic formation. #DelicateArch #VisitUtah #MilkyWay

On this day in 1923, Hovenweep became a National Monument in Utah. This 700-year-old enchanting place is known for its six abandoned Ancestral Puebloan ruins. The multi-storied towers cover more than 20 miles throughout a wilderness of mesas and canyons, sparsely dotted with sage and juniper. #VisitUtah

Ready for a weekend in Park City? Combining its artistic vibe and a deep appreciation for the outdoors, Park City could certainly stake a rightful claim of being the “perfect mountain town.” Ski, explore, taste and experience the boundless winter wonders Utah has to offer! #VisitUtah #SkiUtah 📸: Austin St. John

Adventure to the 73,234-acre wonderland of eroded sandstone, gargoyles, hoodoos, balanced rocks and arches northwest of Moab. From the scenic roads that slice through Arches National Park to the trails that wind among the 300-foot-high towers, it is no wonder this park is one of the most popular in Utah. #VisitUtah

The 2002 Winter Games were held in Salt Lake City and the surrounding Wasatch Mountain communities, where the Olympic Legacy still thrives today. Want to relive an Olympic memory? You can ski the same slopes as Olympians, ride the bobsled track or skate in Olympic facilities. #VisitUtah 📸: Dan Campbell

Catch one of Utah's most magnificent sunsets and stand in awe at this geological marvel. At Goosenecks State Park, capture the winding and twisting wonders, framed by colorful hues; brought forth from a desolate geography when the light is just right. 📸: Michael Kunde #VisitUtah
Check out the link in our bio for a dog-friendly guide when traveling in Utah with your furry best friend for spots you’ll both enjoy. #loveyourpetday #VisitUtah
Tucked away from the highway, and as you start to descend toward Natural Bridges National Monument, the groundcover becomes more luxuriant and the trees taller. #VisitUtah 📸: Jacob W. Frank

One state and fourteen resorts. Have the ski vacation of your dreams — whether you hit the mountain for a few days or a whole week. Looking for deep powder or precision-engineered terrain parks all in one place? There's a Utah resort for that. This weekend invites you to plan a trip to one of the top skiing destinations in the United States! #VisitUtah #SkiUtah #MountainTime 📸: Adam Clark

Travel across more than 800 miles of groomed snowmobile trails, from the red rock canyons of Southern Utah to the rugged mountains in the northern reaches of the state. As you sculpt your way through the snowy myriad trails, experience vast new sights, sounds and adventures! #Snowmobile #VisitUtah 📸: Dan Ransom

Scenic Byway Highway 12 is Utah's nationally-designated All-American Road. Pass through twisting canyons and endless redrock towers this winter. Punctuating the drive are breathtaking snowcapped panoramas, national parks, and monuments.
With diverse terrain and The Greatest Snow on Earth®, Utah continues to redefine freestyle winter sports. Wind-carve your way through Central Utah's Wasatch Plateau. #VisitUtah 📸: Jeremiah Watt

Unlock the secret to Bryce Canyon National Park's wonders with a winter trek to the bottom of the canyon and stroll among hoodoos towering above. Plus, you may have the area all to yourself! #SunsetPoint 📸: Hage Photo

Get your wings this winter and hit the slopes at Snowbird Ski Resort! The mountain rocks 3,240 feet of vertical drop, 2,500 skiable acres, and 85 trails for both skiers and snowboarders. The quest for perfect powder begins in Utah! #LifeElevated #VisitUtah 📸: Scott Markewitz

Keep your life elevated and plan a weekend getaway this winter to some of the highest of Utah's Mighty Five® national parks — road trip from Capitol Reef National Park to Bryce Canyon National Park! Cruise through winding canyons, accompanied by compelling views of snowcapped formations. #LifeElevated #Wanderlust #Utah
Venture to the shores of Bear Lake State Park in Garden City, Northern Utah and marvel at the turquoise blue water, as limestone deposits reflect from beneath. #VisitUtah 📸: Jay Dash

Congratulations to Steinaker State Park, just awarded International Dark Sky Park status. The park staff worked for a year and a half to enhance visitor's view of the stars, located in Vernal. #MilkyWay 📸: Tom Howells

Whether you’re an out-of-state visitor or a local looking for celebrity sightings, on a marathon screening schedule or mixing in fine dining and the area's wintry recreation, the Sundance Film Festival boasts films and experiences for everyone. What are you looking forward to? 📸: Jemal Countess

Need information on the federal government shutdown and its effects on Utah travel? Check out the link in our bio. We'll post updates on the national parks, and have featured alternative destinations and itineraries, including state park adventures and winter ski experiences unaffected by the shutdown. 📸: Sandra Salvas

Experience amazing scenes and things in winter time in Zion National Park that you won't see any other time of year. As always, please take precaution when exploring and don't forget to look up! 📸: Hage Photo

Utah's backcountry and sidecounty are tremendous draws for adventurous skiers and riders thanks to abundant powder snow conditions, diverse terrain and the promise of untracked slopes. 📸: Scott Markewitz

Mark your calendars for the first 2018 National Park Service Free Entrance Day on January 15th and discover a Utah historic site, recreation area, monument or park that may become your new favorite. #VisitUtah
Happy New Year! Wishing you a wonderful 2018 filled with adventure, inspiration, and happiness. #LifeElevated 📷: Adam Clark

Start the New Year off right on January 1st with Utah State Parks at their annual First Day Hikes at Antelope Island, Dead Horse Point and Territorial Statehouse Museum state parks, plus a Full Moon Hike at Great Salt Lake State Park. It's a great family activity! Details in the bio. 📷: ST Smith
Wishing you a Merry Christmas and a warm holiday season filled with family, friends and cheer! PC: Adam Clark
Happy birthday to Capitol Reef National Park, designated on this day in 1971. Hidden arches, massive domes, and deep canyons. What's been your favorite adventure at the park? #redrockcliffs

Winter adventures at @zionnps mean cooler temperatures with parts of the stunning canyon to yourself, ideal for solace seekers and nature photographers. Shorter daylight also brings sunrise, sunset and starry skies closer together — but bundle up for those chilly desert nights! #VisitUtah 📸: Matt Hage

Some of Utah's most colorful #sunsets can be found at the Great Salt Lake. Combinations of orange, purple and pink are often reflected in the 6th largest lake in the U.S. and 34th largest in the world. With no out-flows, the lake is 4 to 8 times saltier than the ocean.

Step up your comfort level at your sleepover with mesas and mountains under a starry sky at Dead Horse Point State Park and stay in one of the park's yurts. Modeled after traditional nomadic tent dwellings of Central Asia, the yurts let you experience an amazing sunrise and sunset at the park. #VisitUtah
Good morning from @altaskiarea, stay tuned for our Instagram Live #WeatherWednesday report featuring our favorite newscaster Evan Thayer! 📸: Lee Cohen

Step up your comfort level at your sleepover with hoodoos under a starry sky at Goblin Valley State Park and stay in one of the park's yurts. Modeled after traditional nomadic tent dwellings of Central Asia, these were the first of their kind in the Utah State Parks, and their popularity has since caught on elsewhere.

Meet ZoZo, one of four rescue pups at Solitude Mountain Resort with extensive training to keep patrons safe. When off duty with the ski patrol team, the cute canines make resort-goers feel all warm and fuzzy, and ZoZo always loves to steal the limelight. Want to meet the other rescue pups? Click the link in our bio! #VisitUtah 📸: Austen Diamond
Experience petroglyph passages and unravel ancient mysteries as you adventure through the exposed secrets of prehistoric times. #petroglyph #VisitUtah #explore #NativeAmericanHeritageDay

It's #NationalTakeAHikeDay and you can find thousands of miles of great hiking trails throughout Utah — past alpine lakes, through dense forests of pine and into mystical desert canyons. What is your favorite Utah hiking trail?

Feel the stillness of the desert as golden autumn melts over the iconic American West - Monument Valley Navajo Tribal Park. Sculpted by the Western winds and shaped by ancestral spirits, towering sandstone formations rest on Utahn sacred lands. #visitutah
Monument Valley Navajo Tribal Park showcases eons of nature's erosive power with distinctive formations unlike anywhere else in the world. #natural #wonder #sculpture #visitutah PC: Anna Day
Discovering the great outdoors is twice as fun with dogs. Here are some of the best destinations for #doglovers in Central and Southern Utah.
